An instrument in writing whereby one person, as principal, appoints another as his agent and confers authority to perform certain specified acts or kinds of acts on behalf of principal. An instrument authorizing another to act as one's agent or attorney. The agent is attorney in fact and his power is revoked on the death of the principal by operation of law. Such power may be either general (full) or special (limited). 

Source: [VA Circuit Court Civil Glossary](http://www.courts.state.va.us/courts/circuit/resources/manuals/cc_manual_civil/glossary.pdf)